quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  6,13,"To Him belongs whatever exists in the day and night. And He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  6,14,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWill I take any guardian other than God, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who provides for all and is not in need of provision?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúI have been commanded to be the first to submit and not be one of the polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  6,15,"Say, ‚ÄúI truly fear‚ÄĒif I were to disobey my Lord‚ÄĒthe torment of a tremendous Day.‚ÄĚ"
  6,16,Whoever is spared the torment of that Day will have certainly been shown God‚Äôs mercy. And that is the absolute triumph
  6,17,"If God touches you with harm, none can undo it except Him. And if He touches you with a blessing, He is Most Capable of everything"
  6,18,"He reigns supreme over His creation. And He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  6,19,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho is the best witness?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúGod is! He is a Witness between me and you. And this Quran has been revealed to me so that, with it, I may warn you and whoever it reaches. Do you ňĻpagansňļ testify that there are other gods besides God?‚ÄĚ ňĻThenňļ say, ‚ÄúI will never testify ňĻto thisňļ!‚ÄĚ ňĻAndňļ say, ‚ÄúThere is only One God. And I totally reject whatever ňĻidolsňļ you associate with Him.‚ÄĚ"
  6,20,Those to whom We gave the Scripture recognize him ňĻto be a true prophetňļ as they recognize their own children. Those who have ruined themselves will never believe
  6,21,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against God or deny His signs? Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed"
  6,22,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day We will gather them all together then ask those who associated others ňĻwith God in worshipňļ, ‚ÄúWhere are those gods you used to claim?‚ÄĚ"
  6,23,"Their only argument will be: ‚ÄúBy God, our Lord! We were never polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  6,24,See how they will lie about themselves and how those ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them
  6,25,"There are some of them who ňĻpretend toňļ listen to your recitation ňĻof the Quranňļ, but We have cast veils over their hearts‚ÄĒleaving them unable to comprehend it‚ÄĒand deafness in their ears. Even if they were to see every sign, they still would not believe in them. The disbelievers would ňĻevenňļ come to argue with you, saying, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  6,26,"They turn others away from the Prophet and distance themselves as well. They ruin none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  6,27,"If only you could see when they will be detained before the Fire! They will cry, ‚ÄúOh! If only we could be sent back, we would never deny the signs of our Lord and we would ňĻsurelyňļ be of the believers.‚ÄĚ"
  6,28,"But no! ňĻThey only say thisňļ because the truth they used to hide will become all too clear to them. Even if they were to be sent back, they would certainly revert to what they were forbidden. Indeed they are liars"
  6,29,"They insisted, ‚ÄúThere is nothing beyond this worldly life and we will never be resurrected.‚ÄĚ"
  6,30,"But if only you could see when they will be detained before their Lord! He will ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúIs this ňĻHereafterňļ not the truth?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúAbsolutely, by our Lord!‚ÄĚ He will say, ‚ÄúThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  6,31,"Losers indeed are those who deny the meeting with God until the Hour takes them by surprise, then they will cry, ‚ÄúWoe to us for having ignored this!‚ÄĚ They will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their sins on their backs. Evil indeed is their burden"
  6,32,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement, but far better is the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter for those mindful ňĻof Godňļ. Will you not then understand"
  6,33,We certainly know that what they say grieves you ňĻO Prophetňļ. It is not your honesty they question‚ÄĒit is God‚Äôs signs that the wrongdoers deny
  6,34,"Indeed, messengers before you were rejected but patiently endured rejection and persecution until Our help came to them. And God‚Äôs promise ňĻto helpňļ is never broken. And you have already received some of the narratives of these messengers"
  6,35,"If you find their denial unbearable, then build‚ÄĒif you can‚ÄĒa tunnel through the earth or stairs to the sky to bring them a ňĻmore compellingňļ sign. Had God so willed, He could have guided them all. So do not be one of those ignorant ňĻof this factňļ"